main event: Sighting of 3 brilliant white objects in a triangular shape flying at high speed observed in Mankato, Minnesota.
interesting points: The objects had an 8 ft. wingspan and maneuvered erratically,The sighting lasted for 2-5 seconds,The weather was clear and visibility was good, The objects disappeared to the west after the observation, Conclusions of the report include the possibility of the objects being a balloon or aircraft reflection.
sighted object: three brilliant white objects in a triangular shape
witness description: ground observer, possibly a pilot from an F-51
